#. Tag: title
#: hacking.docbook:312
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multi-Disc Options"
msgstr "Opciones multidisco"

#. Tag: para
#: hacking.docbook:314
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <link linkend=\"musicbrainz\">MusicBrainz</link>, <link linkend=\"discogs"
"\">Discogs</link>, and <link linkend=\"itunes\">iTunes</link> data sources "
"can fetch multi-disc album information, specifying which tracks each disc "
"contains. By default, the track lists are inserted into separate field, one "
"for each disc. Prior to version 4.0, the track lists were combined. This "
"option provides the pre-4.0 behavior on an individual data source level. Add "
"it to each <emphasis>Data Source</emphasis> section where it is desired."
msgstr ""
"Las fuentes de datos <link linkend=\"musicbrainz\">MusicBrainz</link>, <link "
"linkend=\"discogs\">Discogs</link> e <link linkend=\"itunes\">iTunes</link> "
"pueden extraer información de álbumes multidisco, especificando las pistas "
"que contiene cada álbum. De forma predeterminada, las listas de pistas se "
"insertan en un campo separado (uno para cada disco). Antes de la versión "
"4.0, las listas de pistas se combinaban. Esta opción proporciona el "
"comportamiento previo a la versión 4.0 a nivel de fuente de datos "
"individual. Añádala a cada sección <emphasis>Fuente de datos</emphasis> "
"donde la necesite."

#. Tag: title
#: hacking.docbook:322
#, no-c-format
msgid "Split Tracks By Disc"
msgstr "Dividir pistas por disco"

#. Tag: para
#: hacking.docbook:324
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Setting this to <emphasis>false</emphasis> reverts to pre-4.0 behavior where "
"the tracks are collapsed into a single track list."
msgstr ""
"Si define esta opción a <emphasis>falso</emphasis> se revierte el "
"comportamiento previo a la versión 4.0, donde las pistas se compactan en una "
"única lista de pistas."

#. Tag: userinput
#: hacking.docbook:330
#, no-c-format
msgid "Split Tracks By Disc=false"
msgstr "Dividir pistas por disco=falso"

#. Tag: title
#: hacking.docbook:338
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bibtex Character Translation"
msgstr "Traducción de caracteres Bibtex"

#. Tag: para
#: hacking.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When bibtex files are imported or exported, certain characters are "
"translated between their TeX equivalents and the Unicode characters. Those "
"character mappings are contained in the <filename>bibtex-translation.xml</"
"filename> file, located in the installation data directory. The mappings can "
"be modified, as desired. The key element contains the Unicode character, and "
"the string elements within contain the TeX equivalents, which may be a one-"
"to-many mapping. The first one is the one used when exporting to bibtex."
msgstr "Cuando se importan o exportan archivos de bibtex, ciertos caracteres "

#. Tag: programlisting
#: hacking.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<![CDATA[\n"
"  <key char=\"À\">\n"
"    <string>{\\`A}</string>\n"
"    <string>\\`{A}</string>\n"
"  </key>\n"
"]]>"
msgstr ""
"<![CDATA[\n"
"  <key char=\"À\">\n"
"    <string>{\\`A}</string>\n"
"    <string>\\`{A}</string>\n"
"  </key>\n"
"]]>"
